Step 1: Calculate the Quick Assets.  
• Cash on Hand = 1,254,762.92  
• Bank Deposits = 1,982,606.98  
• Interest Receivable = 7,775.44  
• Accounts Receivable = 335,967.05  

Quick Assets = 1,254,762.92 + 1,982,606.98 + 7,775.44 + 335,967.05 = 3,581,112.39  

Step 2: From the balance sheet, the Total Current Liabilities is given as 3,376,304.04.  
The Quick Ratio is calculated as:  
  Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities = 3,581,112.39 / 3,376,304.04 ≈ 1.06  

Step 3: Next, calculate the Net Profit Margin. From the income statement:  
• Net Profit = 143,922.03  
• Total Revenue = 851,679.79  

Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 = (143,922.03 / 851,679.79) × 100 ≈ 16.90%  

Thus, the final result is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Quick Ratio": "1.06",
    "Net Profit Margin": "16.90%"
  }
}
